                   of Keplerian shear relevant to accretion discs. We find that
                   when the magnetic Reynolds number is kept fixed, the
                   turbulent transport (as measured by the
                   stress-to-thermal-pressure ratio $\alpha$) scales with the
                   magnetic Prandtl number as $\alpha \sim
                   \text\{Pm\}^\{\delta\}$, with $\delta \sim 0.5-0.7$ up to
