                   turbulent dynamics in Fourier space, focusing on the effect
                   increasing Pm has on the transverse cascade -- a key
                   non-linear process induced by the disc shear flow that is
                   responsible for the sustenance of MRI turbulence. Finally,
                   we find that the scaling of turbulent transport with Pm is
                   sensitive to the box vertical-to-radial aspect ratio, as
                   well as to the background shear: tall boxes exhibit weaker
                   scaling compared to cubic boxes, while MRI turbulence in
                   sub-Keplerian shear flows (characteristic of protoneutron
                   stars) exhibits stronger scaling than it does in Keplerian
                   discs.",
  month         =  jun,
  year          =  2022,
